-- Vodafone Plans to Stay in Greece, Chief Colao Tells Kathimerini
-- B y   P a u l   T u g w e l l
-- 2012-03-03T17:41:25Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2012-03-03/vodafone-plans-to-stay-in-greece-chief-colao-tells-kathimerini.html
Vodafone Group Plc (VOD)  has no plans to
leave  Greece  and doesn’t fear the country’s economic situation,
 Kathimerini  said, citing Vodafone Chief Executive Officer
Vittorio Colao.  Vodafone will continue to focus on developing in Greece
strong data infrastructure for person-to-person and machine-to-
machine communications, the Athens-based newspaper cited Colao
as saying in an interview to be published in tomorrow’s edition.  Vodafone is pleased with its co-operation with  Hellas
Online SA (HOL)  in Greece, Kathimerini cited Colao as saying.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Paul Tugwell in Athens at 
 ptugwell1@bloomberg.net   To contact the editor responsible for this story:
